"Monty Python and the Holy Grail," released in 1975, features several prominent members of the Monty Python comedy troupe. The main actors in the film include:

- Graham Chapman as King Arthur
- John Cleese as Sir Lancelot and various other characters
- Eric Idle as Sir Robin and various other characters
- Terry Jones as Sir Bedevere and various other characters
- Michael Palin as Sir Galahad and various other characters
- Terry Gilliam as Patsy and various other characters

These actors showcased their comedic talents through multiple roles in the film, contributing to its unique humor and style.
